The function sets `at_command->id = AT_COPS;` but doesn't initialize the `mask` field. According to the PR description, this creates a use-after-free vulnerability because downstream code relies on the mask to determine whether parameter fields contain valid allocated memory that needs cleanup.

The fix is to add `at_command->mask = AT_COMMAND_NO_PARAM;` to indicate that this command variant has no parameters.

